'''Buddhism in Finland''' represents a very small percentage of that nation's religious practices. According to Statistics Finland, there are 1814 followers of Buddhism in Finland (2017).<ref>[http://pxnet2.stat.fi/PXWeb/pxweb/en/StatFin/StatFin__vrm__vaerak/statfin_vaerak_pxt_016.px/ Population by religious community, age and sex in 2000 to 2017] Statistics Finland's PX-Web databases</ref>

There are currently 12 Finnish cities that have Buddhist temples: in [[Helsinki]], [[Hyvinkää]], [[Hämeenlinna]], [[Jyväskylä]], [[Kouvola]], [[Kuopio]], [[Lahti]], [[Lappeenranta]], [[Pori]], [[Salo, Finland|Salo]], [[Tampere]] and [[Turku]].{{cn|date=July 2016}}

