'''Emma Restall Orr''' (born 1965) is a British [[Neo-druidism|neo-druid]], animist, priest, poet, and author.{{citation needed lead|date=November 2014}} 
<!--No further statement or sourcing to establish "animist", "priest", or "poet" in article.-->

==History==
{{BLP sources section|date=November 2014}}
Restall Orr worked for the [[Order of Bards, Ovates and Druids]] in the early 1990s, becoming an Ovate tutor.{{citation needed|date=November 2014}} In 1993 she became joint chief of the British Druid Order (BDO), staying until 2002.{{Citation needed|date=November 2011}} Together with the Order founder [[Philip Shallcrass]], she developed the BDO into one of the largest and most influential of its time.{{peacock term|date=November 2014}}<ref>Ronald Hutton, 2006, "Witches, Druids and King Arthur," Bloomsbury, PAGE NUMBERS, {{ISBN|185285555X}}.{{page needed|date=November 2014}}</ref>{{page needed|date=November 2014}} Feeling the system of Orders too limiting,{{according to whom|date=November 2014}} Restall Orr created [[The Druid Network]] in 2002,<ref>[https://www.webarchive.org.uk/wayback/archive/20060721120000/http://www.druidnetwork.org/profiles/people/emma_restall-orr.html] </ref> which was officially launched at ''[[Imbolc]]'' in 2003.<ref>[https://www.webarchive.org.uk/wayback/archive/20070602120000/http://www.avalonia.co.uk/books/author_interviews/bobcat_interview.htm] </ref> In 2004, she founded the organization, [[Honouring the Ancient Dead]].

==Gatherings==
Since the late 1990s Restall Orr has organised the largest annual gatherings of Druids and those interested in Druidry,{{citation needed|date=November 2014}} first at The Awen Camp with Philip Shallcrass,{{citation needed|date=November 2014}} then at The Druid Camp since 2001 (with Mark Graham).{{citation needed|date=November 2014}}

==Media attention==
Over the course of her life in Druidry she has been on numerous television and radio programmes in Britain and around the world, featured and quoted in the print media and on the internet.{{citation needed|date=November 2014}} A resume of Emma Restall Orr's media work is provided online, by her agent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.puttick.com/Restall-orr.htm|title=Puttick Agency - Emma Restall Orr|publisher=Puttick.com|accessdate=22 November 2014}}</ref>{{self-published inline|date=November 2014}}

==Personal life==
{{Multiple issues|section=yes|
{{Expand section|small=no|1=place of birth, educational history, and further family information|date=November 2014}}
{{BLP unsourced section|date=November 2014}}
}}
She is daughter of Robin Restall, renowned ornithologist,{{peacock term|date=November 2014}} writer and artist. Her brother is [[Matthew Restall]], history professor and writer.

