Two other publishers have been called Heron Books, both based in London. One published faux-leather classics in the late 1960s and early 1970s<ref>http://www.hcbooksonline.com/blog/?page_id=12</ref> while the other published new fiction and nonfiction as an imprint of [[Quercus (publisher)|Quercus]] from 2011 to 2016.<ref>http://www.thebookseller.com/news/quercus-discontinues-heron-books-322058</ref>
