{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | honorific-prefix = His Excellency | name = Robert Herman Flock | title = [[Bishop]] of [[San Ignacio de Velasco]] in [[Bolivia]] | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | church = | archdiocese = | province = | metropolis = | diocese = [[San Ignacio de Velasco]] | see = | elected = | appointed = November 11, 2016 | term = | term_start = | quashed = | term_end = | predecessor = [[Bishop Carlos Stetter]] | opposed = | successor = | other_post = <!---------- Orders ----------> | ordination = | ordinated_by = | consecration = January 17, 2013 | consecrated_by = [[Tito Solari Capellari]] <!---------- Personal details ----------> | birth_name = Robert Herman Flock | birth_date = {{Birth date|1956|11|04}} | birth_place = [[Sparta, Wisconsin]], United States }}
'''Robert Herman Flock''' (born November 4, 1956) is an [[United States|American]] [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]] who serves as [[bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Ignacio de Velasco]], [[Bolivia]].
==Biography== Born in [[Sparta, Wisconsin]], Flock was ordained to the priesthood on July 9, 1982,<ref name=Lacrosse>{{cite news|title=La Crosse Priest Names Bishop in Bolivia|url=http://lacrossetribune.com/news/la-crosse-priest-named-bishop-in-bolivia/article_6cdb4094-23db-11e2-9da8-001a4bcf887a.html?comment_form=true|accessdate=29 January 2013|newspaper=La Crosse Tribune|date=1 November 2012}}</ref> for the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of La Crosse]], [[Wisconsin]]. Flock received theological training from St. Francis de Salles College Seminary, as well as from the [[Pontifical North American College]] and the [[Pontifical Gregorian University]] in Rome, where he received a degree in [[Biblical Theology]].<ref name=ElDia />
Flock arrived in [[Bolivia]] in 1988, where he began missionary work and priestly ministry in [[Santa Cruz, Bolivia|Santa Cruz]]. He was appointed Assistant Vicar for the Parish of Santa Cruz, and was responsible for pastoral vocations.<ref name=LosTiempos />
On October 31, 2012, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] appointed him to be [[titular bishop]] of [[Forum Popilii]], today [[Forlimpopoli]], near [[Forlì]], in Italy, and auxiliary bishop of the Archdiocese of Cochabamba.<ref name=Lacrosse /><ref name=ElDia>{{cite news|title=Benedicto XVI nombra dos nuevos obispos para Bolivia|url=http://www.eldia.com.bo/index.php?cat=1&pla=3&id_articulo=102664|accessdate=29 January 2013|newspaper=El Día|date=1 November 2012|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=LosTiempos>{{cite news|title=El Papa nombra dos nuevos obispos|url=http://www.lostiempos.com/diario/actualidad/nacional/20121101/el-papa-nombra-dos-nuevos-obispos_190853_405895.html|accessdate=29 January 2013|newspaper=Los Tiempos|date=1 November 2012|language=Spanish|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102063601/http://www.lostiempos.com/diario/actualidad/nacional/20121101/el-papa-nombra-dos-nuevos-obispos_190853_405895.html|archivedate=2 November 2012|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pontifical Acts for Oct 31|url=http://www.ewtn.com/vnews/getstory.asp?number=122109|accessdate=29 January 2013|newspaper=EWTN.com|date=31 October 2012}}</ref> On November 11, 2016, [[Pope Francis]] appointed him as [[bishop]] of [[San Ignacio de Velasco]].
Flock was consecrated bishop on January 17, 2013 by [[Tito Solari Capellari]], [[Salesians of Don Bosco|S.D.B.]], archbishop of Cochabamba, in the [[Cathedral of San Sebastián in Cochabamba|Cathedral of San Sebastián]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Gould|first=Stan|title=Monsignor Flock elevated to bishop in Bolivia|url=http://thecatholictimes.com/monsignor-flock-elevated-to-bishop-in-bolivia-p1466-1.htm|accessdate=29 January 2013|newspaper=The Catholic Times|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130216212123/http://thecatholictimes.com/monsignor-flock-elevated-to-bishop-in-bolivia-p1466-1.htm|archivedate=16 February 2013|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Cheney|first=David M.|title=Bishop Robert Herman Flock Bever|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bflockb.html|work=The Hierarchy of the Catholic Church|accessdate=29 January 2013}}</ref>
